author: Russell Brand
description:
I’m digging into fresh allegations that Klaus Schwab personally ordered the World Economic Forum to manipulate its global competitiveness rankings to make Brexit Britain look worse than it was—while quietly protecting India’s position to woo Narendra Modi. From whistle blower claims of falsified data to misuse of funds and internal s*xual misconduct allegations, it’s a window into how unelected globalists can bend “research” to serve political ends. Brexit wasn’t just opposed in principle—it was undermined in practice, exposing the deep hostility global bureaucracies have toward national sovereignty.
